# Copy this file to ".env" and adjust values as needed.
# Variables defined here are read by Astro at build time and (because they start with PUBLIC_) are also available to client code.

# PUBLIC_DYNAMIC_OG_IMAGE controls dynamic Open Graph image generation.
# - When "true" (default), Astro will:
#   - Generate /og.png for the site and /posts/.../index.png for posts that qualify.
#   - Fetch Google Fonts at build-time to render images (requires outbound network access).
# - When "false", Astro will:
#   - Skip generating dynamic OG images during build (static paths return empty).
#   - Return 404 for the dynamic OG image endpoints at runtime.
#   - Avoid any network calls for Google Fonts during the build, improving reliability in offline/air-gapped CI.
#
# Accepted values (case-insensitive): true/false, 1/0, yes/no, on/off.
# Default if unset: true
#
# Recommended:
# - Local development with internet: leave as default (or set to true).
# - CI/CD or restricted/offline environments: set to false.
#
# Example: disable dynamic OG image generation for faster/offline builds
# PUBLIC_DYNAMIC_OG_IMAGE=false

# Example: explicitly enable (redundant if you leave it unset, since default is true)
# PUBLIC_DYNAMIC_OG_IMAGE=true
